ommunication is critical. However his positive atmosphere suggests he can maintain crew morale, maybe communication can be improved. Also egocentric may affect crew resource management.\n\nB's uncooperative and nasty remarks are severe for crew. A's unfriendly also severe. D's arrogance and hot temper also severe.\n\nThus C likely best.\n\nWe should state our vote for Candidate C, with rationale, and note uncertainties (communication). Also ask other agents if they have any positive evidence of Candidate C's communication or teamwork that could offset negatives.\n\nPublic message: summarize evaluation, state vote, ask if any other info."}
